==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maturely
<hw>Ma*ture"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a mature
manner; with ripeness; completely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With caution; deliberately.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Early; soon.</def> <mark>[A Latinism, little
used]</mark> <rj><au>Bentley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>maturement</ent>⟦br⟧
